description.2: Beverly is adjusting to married life with Dr. Bong, which she agreed to do in order to save Howard's life, but when she comes to find out that Dr. Bong is still planning on killing Howard, all bets are off! Howard and Iris are ready to put a stop to the circus of crime- can they stop the thieving carnies?
description.3: Thing teams up with Nova and Milandra to defeat a new group of foes, the Monitors! But can Thing defeat these enemies without the rest of the Fantastic Four!?
description.5: When the Millenium Falcon is disabled, Han will have to outduel space pirates to survive!
description.6: Adapting Mark Twain's The Prince and the Pauper! In the ultimate switch-up, a young street urchin trades places with a prince who looks just like him!
description.8: The proverbial pot is stirred after a documentary is aired about the Defenders, inviting all heroes to come join the team. Will this unwanted TV time cause tension for the Defenders' current members?
description.9: The fated meeting at last! Ms. Marvel comes face to face with the Kree champion of Earth, Captain Marvel! Will Mar-Vell accept Carol Danvers? And can the two work together to escape from and defeat Ronan the Accuser?
description.11: Moon-Boy wakes to find himself in a glass case, abducted by the "Sky Demons." A hellish series of experiments follow. Meanwhile, Devil, White-Hair, and Stone-Hand find themselves in battle with two alien creatures on their way to the Tower of Death.
description.12: Dormammu has claimed control over Ghost Rider! Enter... the Bounty Hunter.
description.13: Banner faces an identity crisis when trying to reconcile his two halves. Only one man can help Bruce- Doc Samson, PhD!
description.14: During a battle with Unicorn, Tony notices that his foe is being directed a mysterious "Other" from the shadows.
description.15: Paladin, Phantasm, and Marsha Conners trapped in a fatal love triangle!
description.16: As the Asgardian gods and goddesses gather together for the arrival of Ragnarok, Hobbs and his crew get an inside scoop!
description.17: What if Jane Foster found the hammer of Thor? After helping Asgardians fend off Loki, mortal Jane Foster is deemed worthy of Mjolnir. Will Jane still be the love of Thor?
description.18: After just freeing themselves from the control of Mesmero, the X-Men storm the villain's carnival trailer!
description.19: Reed is blasted into outer space to regain his lost powers- but he's not alone! Will the Fantastic Four foil Doom's plan to be the ruler of Earth? Or are they too long out of practice?
description.22: Unaware that Project Pegasus has been infiltrated by members of the Cult of Enthropy, Cap and the Thing allow Wundarr to be tampered with by using the power of the Cosmic Cube!
description.25: The debut of Big Wheel! Spider-Man's most interesting villain smashes onto the scene astride a giant gyroscope. Peter receives doubly bad news in his personal life, while Rocket Racer continues his attack on Spider-Man. But do Spider-Man and Rocket Racer have more in common than they realize?
description.26: The Avengers battle the strange extraterrestrial Collector! Why has he been kidnapping the Avengers?
description.27: After embarking on one of his missions, Captain America is found floating in a river, with no memory of what happened to him the night before! Can Cap gather his memories in time to complete his mission? Find out as it's a race against the clock to stop the Madbomb!
description.29: White Fang, half-dog, half-wolf, goes on an inspirational journey that touches the human heart. Adapting Jack London's classic White Fang.
description.33: Space pirates are using a sonic jammer to take down any and all ships, whether they're Rebel or Imperial!
description.36: The Black Panther races against the clock to stop Jakarra from using the Vibranium Mound to destroy the Earth!
description.40: Captain Marvel goes head to head with -- The Mighty Thor!? What could cause these Avengers-in-arms to fight on opposite sides?
description.41: Richard Rider follows his father to a meeting of the Inner Circle- as Nova! Can Richard save his father from this heinous gang without revealing his identity as Nova?
description.42: Heather Glenn's in trouble as Daredevil races to her rescue only to find battle with Mr. Hyde and Cobra!
description.43: After a prophetic dream about "Sky Demons", Moon-Boy discovers that his nightmare has become a reality. Who are these strange robot creatures falling from the skies? And what plans do they have for Devil?
description.44: Doc Samson revives the dying body of Bruce Banner...by reawakening the Hulk!
description.45: The Armored Avenger goes it alone against the Punisher from beyond! You won't want to miss out on Iron Man's strangest adventure!
description.46: Reporter Harris Hobbs is beginning to remember his time in Asgard- but how?
description.47: Dracula - powerless! Will the legendary vampire fall to an unruly mob?
description.48: Susan, Johnny and Ben are reunited in California- and are abruptly captured by the Invincible Man! Will the team stand united after being so long divided?
description.51: Adapting H.G. Wells' sci-fi horror The First Men In The Moon. And they're not alone…
description.54: Captain America has been poisoned and there’s no known antidote! Falcon is going to have to join forces with Spider-Man if there’s any hope of saving Cap!
description.55: Guest-starring Spider-Man! While playing around with her newly acquired Shadow Cloak, Hellcat accidentally sets the Hulk on a rampage!
description.56: Howard is forced into a circus crime gang, acting as a comedian...and he desperately needs to think of a way out! When Paul and Lee are hospitalized because of the dangerous heists committed by the Circus of Crime, will Howard finally stop this maddening group of thieves?
description.57: Peter Parker makes the biggest decision of his life! Rocket Racer is back in town and is blackmailing businessman Jackson Weele for everything he owns. What has Rocket Racer got his hands on that carries so much value for Weele? And will Spider-Man finally uncover the civilian identity of Rocket Racer?
description.58: The mysterious disappearances of Avengers members continue! Can the remaining team members unravel this enigma?
description.59: Captain America grows suspicious of Veda's alliance to S.H.I.E.L.D. But is it too late when the monstrosity known as Animus appears?
description.60: When Chewie thinks Luke is responsible for an attack on him and Han, the wookie goes on a rampage.
description.64: Ms. Marvel faces off with Centurion! But even when the Avengers arrive to lend a hand, how will they manage to defeat the newest menace in the Marvel Universe - Mystique?
description.69: The Living Pharoah has amplified his powers and has now turned into The Living Monolith!
description.71: The Defenders draw closer to the Cult's innermost secrets, including their base of operation. A mission in Mexico goes horribly awry.
description.72: Paul takes Howard out for a night on the town to blow off some steam. Dr. Bong, as usual, is devising a scheme to take out Howard the Duck. But Beverly is determined she has had just about enough.
description.76: Marvel legends adapt the folklore of The Arabian Nights in a series of thrilling fables.
description.80: Who is the mysterious figure that watches over Moon-Boy and Devil as they sleep? After Moon-Boy does some investigating of his own, he discovers a new race of giants. Do these giants have benevolent or sinister intentions for the Valley of the Flame?
description.81: Dormammu makes himself known! Doctor Strange races to restore the mind of Ghost Rider before Johnny Blaze is lost forever.
description.82: The Leader has seized the Gamma Base and taken its entire team hostage. But Bruce Banner has an idea- he'll use a Hulk robot to take out the villain! What could possibly go wrong?
description.83: Fantasy and fear amid the majesty of Wundagore II! The man and the mayhem! Prepare for the invincible Iron Man!
description.85: In this What If?, Marvel heroes of the 1950's become the first Avengers ! What will this team line-up look like? And what threats will the 1950's Avengers face?
description.86: With Havok in danger, the Beast seeks out his old allies, the X-Men, to rescue him.
description.87: More questions are raised about Reed's mysterious, new job. Meanwhile, Sue discovers that Namor is the head of Imperial Studios!
description.89: Luke is stranded on the water world Drexel and finds himself caught between two opposing forces each looking to possess his ship.
description.90: Spider-Man's retrospective issue! While paying respects at Uncle Ben's grave, Peter reflects on his career as Spider-Man. Who in Peter's life has paid a price because of his alter ego? Will Peter find the happiness that seems to elude him? And can love blossom out of deep despair? Spider-Man's greatest adventures recounted in one tremendous issue!
description.91: The Avengers face off against the menacing merman Tyrak! Plus, Iron Man struggles to discover the secret behind the Avengers' disappearances!
description.92: On his quest to find out more about his past, Steve Rogers sets out to Washington D.C. But to his surprise, Cap finds himself in an all-out battle to the death with his hero! Plus: Veda isn't who she claims to be.
description.93: At the mercy of DEATHGRIP! When the battle seems as though it will never end, Deathgrip forces Captain Marvel to make an impossible choice!
description.96: Nova is faced with a new enemy- Blackout! Can Nova defeat Blackout's Dark-Force before the very sky turns against him?
description.97: Centurion and his mysterious new ally steal a deadly top-secret weapon on a S.H.I.E.L.D. Helicarrier! Only Ms. Marvel can stop them - if she can manage to get through her work day first!
description.99: Daredevil gets ever closer to trail of Purple Man, but once again is cut off by the mercenary Paladin!

3.text: Thing teams up with Nova and Milandra to defeat a new group of foes, the Monitors! But can Thing defeat these enemies without the rest of the Fantastic Four!?

4.text: Durability and extendo arms aside, the Autocrons still prove too insurmountable a foe for Machine Man!

7.text: Captain America recounts a horrifying chapter from his days with the Allied Forces.

8.text: The proverbial pot is stirred after a documentary is aired about the Defenders, inviting all heroes to come join the team. Will this unwanted TV time cause tension for the Defenders' current members?

9.text: The fated meeting at last! Ms. Marvel comes face to face with the Kree champion of Earth, Captain Marvel! Will Mar-Vell accept Carol Danvers? And can the two work together to escape from and defeat Ronan the Accuser?

10.text: Someone’s playing mind games with Spider-Woman, and her hallucinations are nothing short of terrifying! Will Jessica escape the deranged clutches of Hangman? Will Magnus reveal his true nature? Plus, Agent Jerry Hunt is back! But is he too just an illusion?

15.text: Paladin, Phantasm, and Marsha Conners trapped in a fatal love triangle!

20.text: J. Jonah Jameson is prime target #1 for the enraged Scorpion! Blaming the news magnate for his monstrous powers, Mac Gargan will stop at nothing to quash Peter Parker’s boss.

23.text: Spider-Man, Iron Man, and Jean DeWolff. Wraith and Whiplash. Need we say more?

24.text: Doctor Strange and Clea are attacked by mysterious creatures in the New York City sewer system while investigating the death of sewage workers!

30.text: All of Shang-Chi’s allies and enemies come together for a fateful confrontation that will end in death!

34.text: Iron Fist’s life is in jeopardy when Joy Meachum offers Morgan substantial money to shoot Danny Rand! Meanwhile, Power Man seeks out Misty Knight, but falls to Simon Shreeve’s army of robots!

35.text: Humanity's last hope lies in Machine Man – a being struggling to reconcile his emotionality and artificial intelligence.

36.text: The Black Panther races against the clock to stop Jakarra from using the Vibranium Mound to destroy the Earth!

37.text: A MATTER OF NECESSITY To save a galaxy, Star-Lord must undertake a mission of cosmic vengeance. (note: this contains the Star-Lord story only)

38.text: The Invaders star in "Five Against the Flying Death"!

39.text: The vigilante Hangman is as dangerous as he is insane. And although he has pulled the wool over Brother Grimm’s eyes, he is no ally to Spider-Woman. Caught between Brother Grimm and this new masked menace, Jessica’s really in a state of crisis! Especially when Hangman captures Spider-Woman- all to ‘protect’ her, of course.

40.text: Captain Marvel goes head to head with -- The Mighty Thor!? What could cause these Avengers-in-arms to fight on opposite sides?

41.text: Richard Rider follows his father to a meeting of the Inner Circle- as Nova! Can Richard save his father from this heinous gang without revealing his identity as Nova?

42.text: Heather Glenn's in trouble as Daredevil races to her rescue only to find battle with Mr. Hyde and Cobra!

49.text: Hector Ayala’s secret identity is outed. The Lightmaster is dead set on exposing Spider-Man!

50.text: Ten-For, deranged autocrat of the Autocrons, takes on Machine Man!

53.text: VOODOO AND VALOR! Black Panther is in danger, and it’s up to the Thing and Brother Voodoo to save the King of Wakanda from his demise!

61.text: Shang-Chi may have just found a worthy opponent in the brutal pirate Kogar!

64.text: Ms. Marvel faces off with Centurion! But even when the Avengers arrive to lend a hand, how will they manage to defeat the newest menace in the Marvel Universe - Mystique?

65.text: Spider-Woman vs. Brother Grimm! Crime sprees in Los Angeles have left the city unstable. Will Spider-Woman take the law into her own hands, including uncovering the plot of a corrupt senator? And just how is Senator Wyatt connected to the demise of Jessica’s father, Jonathan Drew? Spider-Woman’s demanding answers, and based on her vigilance, she’s due to get some!

67.text: A mission across the pond! Union Jack and Spitfire join the fray in England, alongside Cap, Namor and Torch.

68.text: It’s the Thing and Black Panther against a merciless, undead vampire! Will the two hero’s teamwork be enough to take down this batty menace?

70.text: Back in Manhattan, Stephen Strange is called by Nighthawk to investigate hauntings at the Richmond Enterprises lab.

73.text: Shang-Chi must choose the lady or the tiger -- either way, it's death!

77.text: Luke Cage and Danny Rand encounter a robbery and decide to take action as Power Man and Iron Fist! But during combat, the dynamic duo realizes they’re attacking robots! Just what is going on here?

78.text: Machine Man builds an instrument that allows the alien Autocrons to invade!

84.text: Tigra’s trying to enjoy her Mardi Gras celebration -- but a strange warning from the Cat People really puts her off ease! Is this an opportunity for Tigra to return to her human form?

88.text: Hector and Holly have their date night interrupted by the Enforcers, who are swiftly handled by Spider-Man!

93.text: At the mercy of DEATHGRIP! When the battle seems as though it will never end, Deathgrip forces Captain Marvel to make an impossible choice!

94.text: Without the protection of the Black Panther, Wakanda’s Royal Family stands alone in stopping Jakarra. Meet the Black Musketeers!

96.text: Nova is faced with a new enemy- Blackout! Can Nova defeat Blackout's Dark-Force before the very sky turns against him?

97.text: Centurion and his mysterious new ally steal a deadly top-secret weapon on a S.H.I.E.L.D. Helicarrier! Only Ms. Marvel can stop them - if she can manage to get through her work day first!

98.text: A snafu at the Natural History Museum leads Spider-Woman to battle with Excalibur, a warrior endowed with the mystic powers of Morgan le Fay! In her civilian identity, Jessica finds that a life spent with the High Evolutionary has left her ill-adjusted. And S.H.I.E.L.D. agent Jerry Hunt continues to obsess over the woman who frightens, and excites him! Jessica departs for America, searching for clues to her past.

99.text: Daredevil gets ever closer to trail of Purple Man, but once again is cut off by the mercenary Paladin!
